def clean_data(input_path, output_path):

    df = pd.read_csv(input_path)
    
    # Clean candidate names by stripping whitespace
    df['candidate'] = df['candidate'].str.strip()
    
    # Convert percentages to decimals
    df['percentage'] = df['percentage'].str.rstrip('%').astype(float) / 100

import pandas as pd

def clean_data(input_path, output_path):
    # Read data
    df = pd.read_csv(input_path)
    
    # Clean candidate names by stripping whitespace
    df['candidate'] = df['candidate'].str.strip()
    
    # Convert percentages to decimals
    df['percentage'] = df['percentage'].str.rstrip('%').astype(float) / 100
    
    # Save cleaned data
    df.to_csv(output_path, index=False)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    clean_data('/workspace/election_data.csv', '/workspace/cleaned_election_data.csv')
